  "tolerances": {
    "npv": {
      "abs": 70.0,
      "tolerance_reason": "Bloomberg SWPM screen value remains the assertion target. The calibration's `conventions.ois_compounding = CompoundedWithRateCutoff{cutoff_days: 1}` override aligns the bootstrap-internal float-leg compounding with Bloomberg's SWPM convention, eliminating ~40 NPV of drift vs the registry's ARRC `CompoundedInArrears{lookback_days: 2}` default. Residual ~62 NPV comes from finer-grained schedule/day-count differences (sub-period day counts, stub handling, etc.) that aren't reproducible without internal access to Bloomberg's pricing kernel."
    },
    "par_rate": {
      "abs": 1.5e-06,
      "tolerance_reason": "Bloomberg par coupon to six decimals (percent). With the OIS compounding override matching Bloomberg's SWPM convention, par_rate drift is ~0.014 bp (was ~0.025 bp without override). Residual is from the same higher-order schedule conventions as NPV."
    },
    "dv01": {
      "abs": 0.65,
      "tolerance_reason": "Executable DV01 from Finstack Quant's signed receive-fixed convention against the calibrated curve. The OIS compounding override slightly shifts the bootstrap-implied curve, producing a small (~0.6) DV01 delta vs Bloomberg's screen value. Bloomberg's screen-positive 4523.48 is retained in inputs.source_reference.screen_outputs for provenance."
    },
